{"id":1720,"date":"2023-04-04T05:53:08","date_gmt":"2023-04-04T05:53:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/?p=1720"},"modified":"2023-04-04T05:53:08","modified_gmt":"2023-04-04T05:53:08","slug":"what-are-the-scholarship-requirements-for-international-students-in-canada","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/what-are-the-scholarship-requirements-for-international-students-in-canada\/","title":{"rendered":"What are the Scholarship Requirements for International Students in Canada?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The process of applying for studies in Canada can be overwhelming and expensive. We put together this article about scholarship requirements for international students in Canada to help you apply easier. So if you&#8217;re planning to study in Canada and want to know the scholarship requirements for international students in this country, keep reading.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In this guide:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Entry Requirements for Canadian Universities<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Basic Requirements for Admission<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Scholarship Requirements for International Students<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The CanadaVisa Study Hub $500 Scholarship Contest<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Global Affairs International Scholarship Opportunities for Non-Canadians<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Canada Graduate Scholarships-Master&#8217;s Program<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Ontario Graduate Scholarship<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarship<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Ontario Trillium Scholarship<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">School-Specific Scholarship Awards<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Conclusion<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The government of Canada and many post-secondary schools and institutions offer international students opportunities to gain scholarships, awards, and grants to finance their education and even living fees in this country.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Unlike a loan, money received from an award or scholarship does not need to be repaid. However, you have to meet some university requirements to be eligible for obtaining a scholarship or award. So let&#8217;s start with some entry requirements.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1724\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/close-up-business-man-checking-clipboard-1.jpg\" alt=\" scholarship requirements for International students\" width=\"1472\" height=\"983\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/close-up-business-man-checking-clipboard-1.jpg 1472w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/close-up-business-man-checking-clipboard-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/close-up-business-man-checking-clipboard-1-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/close-up-business-man-checking-clipboard-1-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1472px) 100vw, 1472px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Entry Requirements for Canadian Universities<\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The admission process in Canada may differ from what you have in your country, so make sure you consult the university to apply if you have specific questions. In the meantime, these are some entry requirements to get started:<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>1. Choose a Program that Suits You<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">First of all, choose the degree which is right for you. Almost every program in Canada will be taught in the English language. Whether you&#8217;re an undergraduate or graduated, there are some degrees in many fields across disciplines. Canada is internationally renowned for many programs, including business, science, and humanities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>2. Prepare the Intended Papers<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">A letter of motivation, a recommendation letter, and a previous work portfolio are among the necessary documents commonly required by all universities in Canada. Institutions and universities will also require proof of completion of prior studies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To meet this requirement, send the given university an official transcript from your secondary school if you&#8217;re starting a bachelor&#8217;s or your previous university if you&#8217;re pursuing a master&#8217;s degree or higher. If you&#8217;re not a native English speaker, you may also need to pass an English proficiency test successfully.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>3. Check Admission Requirements<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Depending on the institution or university, specific documentation could be required. Always consult the given university&#8217;s website for particular needs and contact the university office if you have any questions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In Canada, admissions and applications are handled by the university to which you are applying. Potential students are welcomed to apply for several different universities and programs at a time.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>4. Submit Your Application<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Most applications to universities in Canada are made through an online system. Application forms are available through university websites. Sometimes you should pay an application too. After you&#8217;ve completed the application form, add the necessary papers or prepare to mail them to the institution.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>5. It&#8217;s Time to Be Admitted<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Results of admissions are often announced by the end of spring. If you are studying at a private university, they usually ask you to pay the first semester&#8217;s tuition fees. Otherwise, the university where you will proceed with your studies will send you admission confirmation for visa purposes, an official letter of admission, and other information about studying in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>6. Now Apply for Visa<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Upon acceptance into the university, begin the visa application process as soon as possible. Don&#8217;t wait, because the process can take up to sixty days and requires several important papers. International students may not enter and stay in Canada if they don&#8217;t have a proper visa.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">After you&#8217;ve been admitted and have received the visa, it&#8217;s time to go to Canada. Consider the cost of living in Canada and your budget. Once you have that, you can begin looking for accommodation.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1722\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/visa-application-travel-form-concept-3-1.jpg\" alt=\" scholarship requirements for International students\" width=\"1000\" height=\"705\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/visa-application-travel-form-concept-3-1.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/visa-application-travel-form-concept-3-1-300x212.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/visa-application-travel-form-concept-3-1-768x541.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>The Basic Requirements for Admission<\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">While every institution has its international students&#8217; criteria, all applicants worldwide have some basic admission requirements. The followings are standard criteria for admission to Canadian universities:<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>For Bachelor&#8217;s Degrees<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Flexible admission,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">IELTS score, 6 to 6.5 overall,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Or TOEFL score, PBT: 550 min. CBT: 213 min.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>For Master&#8217;s Degrees<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">2 to 3 years full-time work experience,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">GMAT score, 580 to 600 min.,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Or IELTS score, 6.5 overall,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Or TOEFL score, PBT: 580 to 600 min. CBT: 237 to 250 min.,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Four years Bachelor&#8217;s degree, 70% average,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Some institutions may require written samples or copies of published work, portfolios, etc.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>The Scholarship Requirements for International Students<\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">There are specific scholarship requirements for international students in every Canadian university. Following are requirements of popular scholarships for international students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">You should note that the requirements stated in this article may change. It is recommended that you contact the university or organization for international students&#8217; latest scholarship requirements and updated information.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>The CanadaVisa Study Hub $500 Scholarship Contest<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The CanadaVisa Scholarship Contest allows members of the CanadaVisa Study Hub to win USD 500. Every month a member is randomly selected. The contest is designed to support international students and post-graduate workers in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This contest is offered in the Study Hub. This online portal provides many resources and tools to international students looking to make the best of their time in Canada as international graduates and students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for the CanadaVisa Study Hub Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">It would help if you were a new member of the CanadaVisa Study Hub,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Have a valid study permit or post-graduation work permit,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Provide proof of enrolment at a post-secondary university in Canada.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Global Affairs International Scholarship Opportunities<\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In its commitment to participate in research partnerships, Canada collaborates with organizations worldwide to support international education through Canada&#8217;s post-secondary institutions&#8217; opportunities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The value of scholarship offered by Global Affairs Canada varies depending on the duration and level of study. Generally, scholarships range from USD 7200 to USD 14700 for people who have scholarship requirements for international students in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Global Affairs International Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To apply for various scholarships, awards, and fellowships offered through Global Affairs Canada, you should separately consult each scholarship criterion. Also, many scholarships require to apply to the destination institution. Therefore, it is essential to prepare all the necessary documents and coordinate with the destination school.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Canada Graduate Scholarships-Master&#8217;s Program<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Canada Graduate Scholarships-Master&#8217;s Program (CGS M) scholarship program is open to international students on permanent residence status to support their researches in health, natural sciences and engineering, and social sciences or humanities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This award is worth USD 17000 for up to 12 months. Annually, the program helps up to USD 2000 students enrolled in eligible Canadian academic institutions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Canada Graduate Scholarships-Master&#8217;s Program<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To apply for the CGS M, you should be a Canadian citizen or permanent resident of this country;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">be enrolled in, have applied, or will apply for full-time admission to an eligible program at the masters or doctoral level in Canada at a university with a CGS M allocation;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">It would help if you were not a past recipient of CGS M (some exceptions apply);<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">As determined by the host institution, each of the last two completed years of study (full-time equivalent) has achieved a first-class average.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Ontario Graduate Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Ontario Graduate Scholarship or OGS helps graduate students fund their studies in a participating Canadian post-secondary institution. The award is valued at USD 10000 and USD 15000 depending on the number of terms in a study program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This scholarship is funded by Ontario&#8217;s provincial government and the school where the student will attend.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">A prospective recipient is evaluated based on scholarship requirements for international students and academic standing, research skills, and volunteer or leadership experience.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Ontario spends approximately USD 30 million every year to support the OGS program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Ontario Graduate Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If you want to be considered for this scholarship, you should enroll in a graduate program at the masters or doctoral level;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">be registered in full-time studies for two or more terms for the academic of application;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">be on a valid study permit;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">attend a participating Ontario school.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarship or Vanier CGS program is valued at USD 50000. This fund is per year for three years of doctoral studies at a post-secondary institution in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Canadian government introduced the Vanier CGS in 2008 to attract world-class talent to Canada and establish Canada as prime research and higher education locale. The government selects up to 167 new recipients every year.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Scholars are chosen based on academic education and leadership skills at a graduate level. If you want to be considered as a Vanier scholar, you must:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">enroll in a PhD-level program at a Canadian school;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">meet evaluation criteria for leadership, academic excellence, and research potential;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">receive a nomination from the destination post-secondary school of choice.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Ontario Trillium Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Government of Ontario introduced the Ontario Trillium Scholarship or OTS program to help bring the best performing international students to Ontario for completing their Ph.D. studies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">OTS awards are USD 40000 each year and are automatically renewable every three years following the first year. It is essential that a recipient has scholarship requirements for international students and maintains good academic standing and continues to meet the OTS eligibility requirement.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Ontario Trillium Scholarship<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">It would help if you held a valid Canadian study permit to qualify for the OTS;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">intend to proceed full-time graduate studies at the doctoral level in a credible program;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">have outstanding research experience and potential combined with an excellent university academic record;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Be present and registered full-time in the Ph.D. program at the post-secondary school by the award&#8217;s start date and for the program&#8217;s complete duration.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>School-Specific Scholarship Awards<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Universities and colleges of Canada may offer unique entrance scholarships to international students. The awards and fellowships are mostly merit-based and have specific criteria based on academic standing and study duration.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If you could meet scholarship requirements for international students in Canada, some famous awards include:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Humber College International Entrance Scholarships worth between USD 1000 and USD 1500.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University of Manitoba Graduate Fellowships range from USD 14000 to USD 18000 (depending on Master&#8217;s or PhD-level).<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University of Calgary Graduate Awards of USD 1000 to USD 40000 across various fields of study.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">UBC Graduate Global Leadership scholarships to citizens of developing countries valued at USD 18200 per year for four years in doctoral studies at the University of British Columbia.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Dalhousie University Scholarships of up to USD 40000 offered to international students pursuing the university.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1723\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/scholarship-application-form-foundation-concept-2-1.jpg\" alt=\" scholarship requirements for International students\" width=\"958\" height=\"719\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/scholarship-application-form-foundation-concept-2-1.jpg 958w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/scholarship-application-form-foundation-concept-2-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/scholarship-application-form-foundation-concept-2-1-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 958px) 100vw, 958px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Conclusion<\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This article discusses all scholarship requirements for international students in Canadian universities. It also discusses entry requirements and the basic requirements for admission in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Keep in mind that the eligibility requirements and application package often differs from one scholarship to the next. Some scholarships may require a personal essay or request references. Some may offer scholarships based on academic performance, extracurricular achievements, or other skills.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The process of applying for studies in Canada can be overwhelming and expensive. We put together this article about scholarship requirements for international students in Canada to help you apply easier. So if you&#8217;re planning to study in Canada and want to know the s